Course.Title: INTRO TO ENVIRONMENTAL SCIENC
Course.Description: An introduction to the study of the environment as an inclusive system that is connected to the diverse scientific fields of biology, chemistry, geology, hydrology, atmospheric science, climatology and geography. Processes of data collection, sampling, analysis, mapping, modeling and predicting are explored.
